==English==

===Transitive phrasal verb===
{{en-verb2|'''to [[lay]] [[down]]'''|'''[[lays down]]'''|'''[[laid down]]'''|'''[[laid down]]'''|'''[[laying down]]'''}}
# To [[give up]] or [[surrender]] something.
#:''The police urged the gunman to '''lay down''' his weapon.''
# To [[specify]], [[institute]], [[enact]], [[establish]] or [[formulate]] [[rule]]s. 
#:''Let's '''lay down''' the rules right at the beginning, so we are consistent.''
# To [[store]] [[wine]] etc for the [[future]].
# To [[sacrifice]], especially in the phrase "to lay down one's life."

===Intransitive phrasal verb===
'''lay down'''
#Past tense of ''[[lie]]'', in the sense of resting
#:''I feel a bit ill, so I'm going to go '''lay down''' for a while.''

